I need to identify the line items and values related to interest accrued but not yet received from the financial statements.

Looking at the balance sheet, I can see a line item called "Interest Receivable" which represents interest that has been earned but not yet received:
- Initial amount: 0.00 (as of 2023-12-31)
- End amount: 5758.38 (as of 2024-01-30)

This is confirmed in the cash flow statement, which shows "(Increase) Decrease in Interest Receivable" of -5758.38, indicating an increase in the interest receivable amount.

Further confirmation comes from the income statement, which shows "Interest Income" of 5758.38, matching the end amount in the balance sheet.

The Interest Receivable line item represents exactly what we're looking for - interest that has accrued but has not yet been received by the company.
